3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly using a premium/discount formula based on the perpetual contract's price deviation from the ATOM spot index. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per hour to prevent extreme market conditions. Funding payments occur automatically at each hour mark, with long positions paying when rates are positive and receiving when negative. Bluefin's Sui-based infrastructure enables near-instant settlement of funding payments with minimal gas costs."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM perpetual futures exhibit significant funding rate volatility due to Cosmos ecosystem developments and staking yield dynamics. The hourly funding frequency on Bluefin creates 24 arbitrage opportunities per day versus 3 on traditional exchanges. ATOM's position as an interchain infrastructure token generates consistent trading interest, maintaining adequate liquidity for funding rate strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM funding rates on Bluefin typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per hour, with spikes during major Cosmos ecosystem announcements or IBC protocol updates. The hourly reset creates more stable rate patterns compared to 8-hour cycles, reducing extreme negative funding periods. Funding rates tend to correlate with ATOM staking yield changes, often turning negative during high staking reward periods when spot demand exceeds perpetual demand. Historical data shows funding rate volatility increases significantly during Cosmos Hub governance proposals and major validator events."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's hourly funding provides 8x more arbitrage entry points than traditional exchanges, allowing for precise delta-neutral positioning. Traders can capitalize on short-term funding rate spikes by opening opposite positions between Bluefin and 8-hour funding exchanges. The low 0.02% maker fees on Bluefin reduce arbitrage costs, improving profit margins on smaller funding rate differences. Sui's fast block times enable rapid position adjustments when funding rates shift unexpectedly, providing competitive advantage over Ethereum-based perpetual DEXs."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM's interchain nature creates basis risk when funding rate arbitrage positions experience divergent price movements across different blockchain ecosystems. Bluefin's relatively low overall volume may result in slippage during large position entries or exits, particularly for ATOM/USDT which maintains mid-tier volume. The early-stage Sui ecosystem presents smart contract risk and potential protocol upgrades that could affect perpetual contract mechanics. Traders should monitor Cosmos Hub validator set changes and staking parameter updates that can create sudden funding rate shifts outside normal market patterns."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does ATOM funding rate update on Bluefin compared to other exchanges?","answer":"Bluefin updates ATOM funding rates every hour, providing 24 funding periods per day compared to 3 on most centralized exchanges. This creates significantly more arbitrage opportunities and allows for more precise risk management in delta-neutral strategies."},{"question":"What makes Bluefin's order book model different for ATOM perpetuals?","answer":"Bluefin uses an institutional-grade matching engine on Sui that provides order book depth similar to centralized exchanges but with DEX benefits like self-custody. The order book model offers better price discovery for ATOM perpetuals compared to AMM-based perpetual DEXs, leading to more accurate funding rate calculations."},{"question":"How does Sui's infrastructure impact ATOM funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"Sui's parallel execution and fast finality enable near-instant funding payment settlement and rapid position adjustments. The low transaction costs on Sui make frequent arbitrage trades economically viable even for smaller funding rate differences that wouldn't be profitable on Ethereum-based DEXs."},{"question":"What are the main risks of ATOM funding rate arbitrage on Bluefin?","answer":"Key risks include Bluefin's relatively low volume causing slippage, Sui ecosystem smart contract risks, and ATOM's exposure to Cosmos governance events that can create sudden funding rate shifts. Traders should also consider the early-stage nature of the Sui DeFi ecosystem and potential protocol changes."}]}]
